{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"21d85c7a-d047-4086-8132-50251bc4035c","content":"Good news — in .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft Testing Platform **natively**. You **no longer need** `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`. That property was the opt-in bridge for .NET 9; in .NET 10 it's the default behavior.\n\nYou can simplify your csproj:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_017aCPJJ9ZYhsmRjWv8ybV9q","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01GiSLdupsF3TYLBddSxtgVH","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-10c6b325909a424cacbffbacb7eef5a1/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-10c6b325909a424cacbffbacb7eef5a1/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"c4d6a71e-da12-4c3a-bb71-6ea9d0615f7c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK and wants to know about native MTP support. Let me provide the answer.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. Starting with .NET 10 SDK, MTP is the default test runner protocol, so you can remove that property.\n\nLet me also check if there's anything else to consider.\n\nKey points:\n1. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses MTP natively - no need for `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`\n\n\n2. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property can be safely removed from your project\n3. However, `EnableMSTestRunner` is still required if you want to generate the test executable, as it controls whether the MSTest runner entry point gets created","outputTokens":495},"id":"ba332385-4c7c-4d4b-9c1f-72dacb753493","timestamp":"2026-04-07T13:06:46.423Z","parentId":"da6dca8f-d461-4634-b884-288899c65468"}
